  "body": "The ERC-721 implementation lacks the zero address requirements that are present in ERC-20. This allows the zero address to theoretically transfer any token at will, since it has infinite approval over any token that is not explicitly approved to a different address.\r\n\r\nAll though this is a hyper-theoretical vector, it is inconsistent with other OpenZeppelin standards.\r\n\r\n**ðŸ’» Environment**\r\n[ERC721@4e2641a9151fcbb0cd59126a52040fea68ecb807](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/1baa009266425400f289449f0a373fa60e23ecae/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol)\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/1baa009266425400f289449f0a373fa60e23ecae/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol#L152-L161\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/1baa009266425400f289449f0a373fa60e23ecae/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol#L234-L238\r\n\r\n",
